We had our first experience with Benkay last night, it was recommended by my son and friends that study at USM.  We are definetly Sashimi lovers and accompany it with a few rolls so I picked the Volcano (which I had heard was really good) and the Spicy Scallop Maki. When we got home and opened the bag, I was puzzled at what I saw, never seen rolls like these before! The Volcano is huge and a deal at 22$. By far, the most scrumptious "roll" I have ever eaten! If you love scallops, avocado and Tempura, you will be in heaven! Sashimi was fresh, well priced  and tasty, Toro was to die for! The lunch box for the day was vegetable tempura, chicken teriyaki, Shumai, and your favorite roll sushi. I made a salmon and cucumber roll. They are all delicious. Above all, it was nice to have eaten freshly caught sea urchins in this area. It is wonderful that you can eat the highest quality sea urchin without alum. I’m not that picky when it comes to sushi, I’m pretty happy with a veggie roll from the grocery store but if I’m going to pay 30+ dollars for dinner and delivery, I want to at least want to eat my dinner and this just disappointed me. She said she had missed us ordering them. I didn't time it but it was a long wait before we finally got our dinners and everyone else in the party was done eating. There did not appear to be any rush on getting our dinners to us after the error was discovered and they were delivered without apology. Under the circumstances our dinners should have been comped or at the very least we should have been offered a glass of wine or a drink to have while we waited.

My fiancé read good reviews of this place on Facebook. We checked the pictures of the dishes and they seemed great. We went on a Saturday at noon and the restaurant was almost empty. We asked for the menus and to our surprise, none of the dishes posted on their Facebook account could be found there. Either the choices were too much (like a $35 huge meal) or too small (appetizers). I felt disappointed (and a bit deceived) because I couldn't find anything I wanted to try, and I am a fan of Asian food.  I also forgot to mention we arrived with our 3-year-old. I could tell the owner (or manager, not sure) was NOT pleased with us because of it. She was constantly hovering over him despite me being on top of him. The worst was when she wiped his face just mere seconds after he had taken a bite.  We quickly finished our entrees (which were pretty unremarkable) and asked for the bill. Since parking is impossible in Portland (and given the fact that the nice weather meant TONS of tourists), my fiancé asked the same woman if we could leave our car in their parking lot for a short time (he was expecting even paying a small fee for that). Her response: "What car do you have?"  "A red Camry"-we replied. "If I come out and your car is here, I'll have your car towed".  Now we know why this place was empty. Do yourself a favor a go someplace else. There are plenty of good Asian restaurants in Portland that have better service and food.
